    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Hand-Holding Simulator</strong> is a game about maximizing your love. You will curate <i>Affirmations</i> to reinforce your relationship, commit <i>Acts of Service </i>as they appear, and spend<i> Quality Time</i> to get the most out of every moment. Eventually you'll be able to afford<i> Gifts</i> for your partner, and they'll be able to express themselves as they please.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This incremental idle game is designed to offer more variance than others in the genre. As<i> you collect Affirmations</i> randomly, you'll have to make decisions about which ones are worth holding on to.<i> Affirmations</i> have a wide range of effects, and you'll need to find ways for them to work together.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><i>Acts of Service</i> are popups that appear on screen and provide large benefits on their completion. Failing an<i> Act of Service</i> has negative consequences, so you'll need to sacrifice valuable hand-holding time to get them done. You can purchase higher levels of these Acts, which improves their benefits and minimizes their harm.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Once you've collected enough love, you can buy your partner<i> Gifts</i>. These are displayed beautifully on them, and you can dress them up as you'd like. Each<i> Gift</i> also has a passive effect that will be applied on purchase, making future progression easier.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >All of this takes away from the most important piece of the puzzle:<i> Holding Hands.</i> The longer you hold, the more love you earn.<i> Hand-Holding Simulator</i> is capable of handling numbers up to 1 x 10^1000, so you will certainly find fulfillment somewhere along the way.</p>",
